The Alex Jones Show
Friday, 12 July 2013


[sebaygo1]


Show Description
................

From the Infowars web site :: On this Friday, July 12 edition of The Alex Jones Show, Alex confronts the prospect George Zimmerman will be acquitted in the Trayvon Martin case and riots will erupt across America, a possibility exploited by the New Black Panthers who are converging on Sanford, Florida, where the trial is concluding. 

Alex also talks about pervasive NSA surveillance and the further encroachment of a high-tech Stasi surveillance state with guest Wayne Madsen, who will be in-studio today. Madsen, a former NSA employee, is one of America's foremost investigative journalists. He hosts a blog, The Wayne Madsen Report. 

Alex also talks with James O'Keefe, the founder of Project Veritas and author of Breakthrough: Our Guerilla War to Expose Fraud and Save Democracy, a blockbuster book that documents his efforts to expose the duplicity of Planned Parenthood, ACORN, Medicaid, NPR, the New Jersey Educational Association, labor unions and politicians.
